Practical 11 – Creating Maven Project in Eclipse
Aim
To create a Maven-based web application in Eclipse and run it using Tomcat. Also to develop a simple calculator web application using JSP and Servlet.

Part A – Hello World Web Application using Maven
Step 1: Open Eclipse IDE.
Step 2: Click File → New → Maven Project.
Step 3: Uncheck 'Create a simple project (skip archetype selection)' and click Next.
Step 4: In the filter search box type 'webapp'.
Step 5: Select 'maven-archetype-webapp' and click Next.

Step 6: Enter the following project details:
GroupId: com.mywebapp
ArtifactId: MyWebApp
Version: 0.0.1-SNAPSHOT
Package: com.mywebapp

Step 7: Click Finish. Maven will generate the project structure.
Step 8: Right click the project → Run As → Maven Install to build the project.
Step 9: A WAR file will be created inside the 'target' folder.
Step 10: Right click project → Run As → Maven Build.
Step 11: In Goals type: tomcat7:run and click Run.
Step 12: Open browser and go to http://localhost:9090/MyWebApp to see Hello World page.

Part B – Calculator Web Application using JSP and Servlet
Step 1: Open the existing Maven project created in Part A.
Step 2: Go to src → main → webapp → index.jsp.
Step 3: Replace the existing code in index.jsp with calculator form code.
Step 4: Go to src → main → java folder.
Step 5: Right click → New → Class.
Step 6: Enter Class Name: CalculatorServlet and Package: com.mywebapp.
Step 7: Add servlet code inside CalculatorServlet.java.
Step 8: Open src → main → webapp → WEB-INF → web.xml.
Step 9: Add servlet configuration and servlet mapping in web.xml.
Step 10: Save the project.
Step 11: Right click project → Run As → Maven Build.
Step 12: In Goals type: tomcat7:run.
Step 13: Open browser and go to http://localhost:9090/MyWebApp.
Step 14: Enter two numbers and select an operation.
Step 15: The calculated result will be displayed in the browser.

